page.title: 09COOLEY SPRINGS WOOD,ROXWELL
page.content: Cooley Spring is a little clump of trees in the middle of two fields. There is a foot path up to it. One of the things that puzzled us was why had the farmer left only these trees in the middle of two fields. We came to the conclusion that it was problably too boggy. When we went in our conclusion seemed right. Inside it was peaceful, quiet and lived up to its name because a cool breeze blew all the time. Only a few birds sang while we were walking through. The word spring is used as there is a fresh spring somewhere in the small wood. Another reason why it is so muddy is the rain comes down and lays on the ground and the sun can't evaporate it. One of the trees in Cooley Spring had a branch that had started growing round the trunk. It has stopped growing half way up.
